<div class="res-text richtextContent background-hidden" id="b6b9a8fc-808d-4d1a-ba38-9ed5c5b8e9cb" >

    <p>The central design theme is the permanent pedestrianization of Gould Street—raising the roadway to make it level with the walkway, prohibiting vehicular access except for emergency services, and establishing cycling dismount zones.</p> 
<p>Other improvements include additional outdoor lighting, increasing opportunities for public art installations, adding biodiverse plantings, replacing end-of-life trees and other site furnishings to improve the safety and accessibility of our shared public spaces.</p>
    





